name: Knotted Rope Canyon
description:
Introduction

A blast. Nearly 50 potholes and pools. Slides. Sublime scenery. Be sure to take the 5 minute side track on the approach to the edge of the 600 foot cliff for westerly views of the striking labrynth that is the western Swell.

Approach

Descent

Exit

Hike up the Muddy is recommended for the views and to cool off. Petroglyphs, mine ruins.

Red tape
